              A mediocre lobbyist will give you vague answers about "Capitol connections" and "legislative experience." An exceptional lobbyist will provide specific examples, specific names, and specific strategies—because they've done the work.
            </p>

            <p>
              The difference between the two? It's the same difference between having a meeting with a legislator and actually influencing legislation. One is window dressing. The other is what wins require.
            </p>
